   LIQUIDITY-TRAP (Undated) _ Anyone who lived through the Great
Depression or studied economics in its aftermath quickly learned
that even when government prodded people to spend more, they would
not do so in scary times. Then came the prosperous decades, when
the image of the catatonic consumer faded from college courses.
Now, suddenly, it is coming back. By Louis Uchitelle.
