<P>
   EDITORIAL-PRAYER - If God reads all fine print, those who
portray as ``anti-prayer'' the opponents of a prayer resolution in
the House of Representatives may have some explaining to do to
their maker. For ``anti-prayer'' is not the truth. Opponents of the
resolution for a ``day of solemn prayer, fasting and humiliation
before God'' had virtuous reasons to oppose it, even as prayer and
fasting are virtues unto themselves. (Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
THURSDAY FOR SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   MONTYPYTHON-MEANING - What is it about this 30-year-old comedy
troupe that continues to attract - and encourage - nonsensical
behavior? A look at the television series Monty Python's Flying
Circus. (Yoakum, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED FOR SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN - I think that operating a motor vehicle on a
public road is a privilege, not a right. I also believe that the
requirements to obtain a driver's license should be more like the
requirements to obtain a pilot's license. Here's why. (Rowland
Nethaway is senior editor of the Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED FOR
SATURDAY
</P>
