</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-PROTESTS (Novi Sad) _ An anti-Milosevic demonstration is
planned in this major Serbian city on the Danube that was bombed
heavily during the NATO campaign. An earlier rally in another city
drew 10,000. By Blaine Harden.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-ARRESTS (Mitrovica) _ Problems with Serb ``provacateurs''
and paramilitaries: French arrest a Serbian gang leader in
Mitrovica, Dutch arrest some Interior Ministry police, U.S. troops
have arrested five Yugoslav Army soldiers. By Carlotta Gall.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OTHER INTERNATIONAL &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   NIRELAND-TALKS (Belfast, Northern Ireland) _ Northern Ireland
talks resume in what is believed to be a final make-or-break
session. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS (Jerusalem) _ Developments in the dispute in
Israel over President Clinton's remark on Thursday that Palestians
should be allowed to live ``wherever they want to live.'' Ehud
Barak, the prime minister-elect, calls PLO chief Yasser Arafat for
the first time. By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
