<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, July 2 --
Psychology Software Tools Inc. of Pittsburgh won a $803,180
contract from the National Institute of Neurological Disorders and
Stroke in Bethesda, Md., for research and development.
</P>
<P>
   News Printing Co. Inc. of Claysburg won a $222,357 contract from
the U.S. Government Printing Office in Washington, D.C., for
printing services.
</P>
<P>
   Chivers Construction Co. Inc. of Fairview won a $1 million
contract from the National Park Service in Denver, Colo., for
property maintenance and repair.
</P>
<P>
   SKF Industries of Kulpsville won a $58,000 contract from the
Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for bearings.
</P>
<P>
   G&AMP;W Roofing &AMP; Construction Inc. of Eighty Four won a $612,000
contract from the General Services Administration in Philadelphia
for property mantenance and repair.
</P>
<P>
   Lockheed Martin Corp. of Philadelphia won a $69.4 million
contract from the Navy in Patuxent River, Md., for guided missiles.
</P>
<P>
   Wheeler Bros. Inc. of Somerset won a $998,169 contract from the
Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for vehicular equipment
components.
</P>
<P>
   LRG Corp. of Jeannette won a $139,008 contract from the Defense
General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for lab equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Container Research Corp. of Glen Riddle won a $698,232 contract
from the Navy in Philadelphia for containers.
</P>
<P>
   Container Reserach Corp. of Glen Riddle won a $1.1 million
contract from the Navy in Philadelphia for containers.
</P>
<P>
   Keystone Aerial Surveys Inc. of Philadelphia won a $74,710
contract from the USDA in Salt Lake City, Utah, for photography
services.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Co. of Philadelphia won a $723,977 contract from the Navy
in Patuxent River, Md., for engine condition control systems.
</P>
<P>
   Kampi Components Co. Inc. of Bristol won a $70,720 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for engine
accessories.
</P>
<P>
   Utilities Forestry Services Inc. of Clearfield won a contract
for $144,965 from the Army in Baltimore, Md., for pesticide
applications.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing (Rotorcraft) of Philadelphia won a $1.3 million contract
from the Navy in Patuxent River, Md., for aircraft parts.
</P>
<P>
   Jay Bee Machine Works Inc. of Glenside won a $53,220 contract
from the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for
bearings.
</P>
