contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   STUNT-KID (Los Angeles) _ A father and son daredevil team will
jump on a single motorcycle between ramps set 10 feet apart! And
the father, ``Super Joe'' Reed, of Winnetka, will be blindfolded
while his son, 5-year-old ``Super Joey'' Reed, sits on the gas
tank. He says it will get him into the Guinness Book of World
Records. By Jesse Hiestand. (Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news file.)
</P>
<P>
   YORK-AUTONATION (Los Angeles) _ Terry York's auto retailing
empire, which stretches from the Santa Clarita Vallley to
Huntington Beach, is being bought by a Florida-based company that's
been expanding in Southern California. Terms were not disclosed.
The purchase by Auto Nation Inc. of Fort Lauderdale makes that
company the dominant player at the Valencia Auto Mall. By Greg
Wilcox. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
