<P>
   MOON-ICE (Houston) _ A team of scientists from the University of
Texas has devised a novel strategy to provide the strongest
evidence yet that the moon harbors frozen water. On July 31 the
Lunar Prospector probe will plunge into a south pole crater,
thought to hold deposits of ice from colliding comets. By MARK
CARREAU. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   AIR-FORCE-RECRUITING (San Antonio) _ For the first time since
Jimmy Carter was president, the Air Force won't find enough
recruits to fill its enlisted ranks. The service says it will fall
2,500 recruits short of its goal in the fiscal year ending Sept.
30. By SIG CHRISTENSON. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   DRUGS-TEENS (Laredo, Texas) _ Authorities believe drug smugglers
are enlisting teen-agers in increasing numbers to skirt adult laws.
In one bold example, a 16-year-old girl speeding through the
streets of Laredo was caught with $32 million worth of cocaine
openly stacked in the bed of her pickup truck, federal officials
say. By DANE SCHILLER. (Already filed.)
