   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   WORKING-COLUMN (Atlanta) _ The ``bathrobe syndrome'' occurs when
a recovering employee, who is hurt in a non-job-related injury,
languishes at home alone during the day. Jerry Boyer, president of
the Precertification Center in Camp Hill, Pa., has a few ideas on
how to help these workers. By L.M. SIXEL. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTER-COLUMN (Undated) _ If you're using e-mail, Eudora is
the way to go. It's better than Netscape's Messenger; Microsoft's
Exchange, Outlook Express and Outlook; America Online's e-mail
component; even Pegasus, the other top free mail software program.
The latest version of Eudora Pro, 4.2, is the best yet. Its new
