<P>
   DEMOCRATS-RURAL (Washington) _ To win back the House in 2000,
Democrats will have to rely on Democratic anti-abortion and pro-gun
conservatives running in rural districts that were fertile
Republican turf for decades. This strategy, which helped Democrats
chip away at the GOP majority in 1998, was thrown into doubt
recently when a prominent Democrat, Rep. Patrick Kennedy, D-R.I.,
said the party had ``written off the rural areas'' in 2000. By DAN
FREEDMAN. (Filed Thursday.)
