<P>
   AIRFORCE-IMMIGRANTS (McCHORD AFB, Wash.) _ Joachim and Lizette
Camacho are highly regarded young professionals in the Air Force,
but they face a bureaucratic dilemma that could abort their
military careers before they get off the ground. The young married
couple are not U.S. citizens. They were qualified to enlist in the
Air Force but face discharge should they fail to become U.S.
citizens by the end of their four-year enlistments.
