<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, JULY 3
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-BUSH-DONATE-NYT (moved on Thursday, July 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, July 1,
about the Bush campaign treasury and its effect on the Presidential
contest included an incorrect figure for the spending ceiling in
New Hampshire imposed by the Government on candidates who accept
Federal matching funds for the primary season. It is $661,200, not
$6.6 million.
</P>
<P>
   BC-POLITICAL-BRIEFS-NYT (moved on Thursday, July 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, July 1,
about AIDS protesters misstated an estimate of the number of them
who showed up at a political appearance in Philadelphia by Vice
President Al Gore. It was 300, not 3,000.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MRSCLINTON-MEDICARE-NYT (moved on Thursday, July 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, July 1,
about Hillary Rodham Clinton's appearance with Senator Charles E.
Schumer and other New York leaders at a White House meeting to
argue against proposed cuts in Medicare misstated the estimated
cost to New York State teaching hospitals. Senator Schumer says it
is $3.2 billion over the next 10 years; $39 billion is his figure
for hospitals nationally.
</P>
<P>
   BC-VALDEZ-THEATER-NYT (moved on Monday, June 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 28,
about a theater festival in Alaska celebrating the 40th anniversary
of the Off Broadway movement misstated the location of Independence
Community College, from which the event's founder came. It is
Independence, Kan., not Independence, Mo.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-SIDNEY-NYT (moved on Wednesday, June 30)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Sylvia Sidney sent by the New York Times News
Service on Wednesday, June 30, misspelled her original surname. It
was Kosow, not Kossow.
</P>
<P>
   The obituary also omitted two survivors. They are her
half-brothers, Albert C. Kosow of Fort Lauderdale, Fla., and Edgar
J. Kosow of Plantation, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   BC-WOODWARD-BOOK-REVIEW-NYT (moved on Wendesday, June 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June
30, about ``Shadow: Five Presidents and the Legacy of Watergate,''
by Bob Woodward, included the book's incomplete version of a
quotation from President Gerald R. Ford. In his second
election-year debate with Jimmy Carter in 1976, Mr. Ford said that
``there is no Soviet domination of Eastern Europe and there never
will be under a Ford Administration.'' The book omitted
``Eastern.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
