<P>
   AMERICA-ONLINE (Undated) _ Having turned itself in a few years'
time from an object of sneering into the world's most valuable
media company, America Online now is at work on fulfilling its
founder, Stephen Case's vision: to be as important a medium as the
telephone or the television. By Saul Hansell. &UR;  &LR; (Moved0.
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic and Photo.
</P>
<P>
   BEAR-STEARNS-HARRITON (Undated) _ Profane and imperious, Richard
Harriton has for two decades run Wall Street's biggest clearing
operation, the Bear Stearns Securities Corp., with an iron hand. A
tough guy up from the streets of Brooklyn, N.Y., his
us-against-them view of the world meshed nicely, associates say,
with Bear Stearns's macho culture and obsession with the bottom
line. But Harriton apparently failed to recognize that when the
``them'' shifted a few years ago, from his competition on Wall
Street to securities regulators and prosecutors, the game changed.
By Gretchen Morgenson. (Moved).
</P>
