week. With the laboriously negotiated permission of rabbis, a dozen
ultra-Orthodox Israelis are stepping out of their cloisstered
religious universe to train in a three-year social work program at
Bar Ilan, one of Israel's two largest universities. (Rina
Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo)
